com.camerontec.catalys.util

Class FIXApplVerID

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.FIXApplVerID

  • public class FIXApplVerID
extends Object
    Utility class for conversion of ApplVerID enumerated value to Version and from Version to enumerated value, plus utility functions to get FIX version and transport version from ITagValues.

    From FIX 5.0 release notes:

    ApplVerID is an enumerated field. These enumerations are used to express prior versions of FIX inclusive of FIX 4.0, 4.1, 4.2, 4.3 and 4.4 as well as the most recent version, FIX 5.0. Going forward, service packs will be applied to the base version, in this case FIX 5.0, and will be identified as FIX Version + Service Pack . This means that FIX 5.0 will be represented as an enumeration (7) rather than as an actual value in the ApplVerID field. Service Pack identifiers will consist of the base FIX version, the service pack number for that version, and the date the service pack was released. For example, the assigned value for service pack 1 may be FIX 5.0 SP1 June 30, 2007.

      • getFixVersion

        public static String getFixVersion(ITagValues message)
        Get fix version from message BeginString tag or ApplVerId tag depending on BeginString tag value.
        Parameters:
        message - Message
        Returns:
        Null if tag BeginString not in message. If BeginString starts with "FIX." it's substring value after "FIX.". If BeginString starts with "FIXT." application version from enumerated ApplVerID tag value, if tag present. Null otherwise.
